    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "This seems kind of pointless because if you are doing this in `lsp_enable_callback`, that means it only works the first time. Other buffers in the future will use whatever CWD was when `vim.lsp.enable()` was called, which will often be wrong.\r\n\r\nInstead you probably want to define `reuse_client()` which checks CWD and decides whether to reevaluate the config?",
